			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">On Linux, we currently use modify_ldt() to set up segmentation on x86-32.  
This places a limit on the number threads we can support:  The number of 
possible x86 segment selector values is 8192.  We could get around this 
limit by using set_thread_area() instead.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-05-10T21:38:14.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-05-10T21:38:14.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Assigned</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
